-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Astrazeneca, Deutsche Bank, Allianz SE 
-- 
-- Tue May 27, 2014 02:20AM EDT
-- None



May 27 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Astrazeneca, Deutsche Bank and Gazprom, on Tuesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Astrazeneca <AZN.L>: SocGen cuts to sell from hold  * Allianz SE <ALVG.DE>: Berenberg raises price target to 152 euros from 150 euros; buy  * Gazprom <GAZPq.L>: Erste Group raises to hold from sell * Speedy Hire <SDY.L>: Cantor raises to hold from sell; price target to 55p from 51p   Following is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Tuesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.   * Allianz SE <ALVG.DE>: Berenberg raises price target to 152 euros from 150 euros; buy  * Astrazeneca <AZN.L>: SocGen cuts to sell from hold  * Astrazeneca <AZN.L>: SocGen cuts price target to 3600p from 4661p  * Banco Comercial Portugues <BCP.LS>: SocGen starts with buy rating  * Bayer AG <BAYGn.DE>: SocGen cuts price target to 90 euros from 94 euros; rating sell  * Easyjet <EZJ.L>: JP Morgan cuts target price to 1909p from 1965p; rating overweight * Gazprom <GAZPq.L>: Erste Group raises to hold from sell * Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE>: RBC cuts target price to 34 euros from 36 euros; sector perform * Magnit <MGNTq.L>: JP Morgan cuts to neutral from overweight  * Mediaset <MS.MI>: Berenberg raises price target to 3.65 euros from 3.60 euros; rating buy  * Nokia <NOK.N>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to $11 from $10.25; rating buy  * Novartis AG <NOVN.VX>: SocGen raises price target to Sfr 93; rating buy  * Recticel SA <RECT.BR>: ING raises price target to 8.50 euros from 7.60 euros; rating buy  * Ryanair <RYA.I>: JP Morgan raises target price to 8.15 euros from 7 euros; overweight  * Smiths Group <SMIN.L>: Morgan Stanley cuts target price to 1481p from 1536p; overweight * Speedy Hire <SDY.L>: Cantor raises to hold from sell